OL,6,FFigures from the Institute for Fiscal
OL,7,FStudies found "cheapflation" between
OL,8,F2021 and 2023 meant poorer households
OL,9,Fpaid 29.1% more for their food over
OL,10,Fthe period, while much wealthier
OL,11,Fhouseholds only had a 23.5% increase.
OL,13,FInflation measures the speed at which
OL,14,Fprices are rising year-on-year and is
OL,15,Fkeenly watched by government, business
OL,16,Fand economists.
OL,18,FInflation hit a peak of 11.1% in
OL,19,FOctober 2022, after a sharp rise in
OL,20,Fenergy prices sparked by Russia's
OL,21,Finvasion of Ukraine.
